# Introduction

StudentStatsHelper is a small R package designed to help students complete common introductory statistics tasks. It focuses on readable output instead of complicated code.

# Descriptive statistics

```{r eval=FALSE}
library(StudentStatsHelper)
student_summary(student_scores$final_exam)
```

# Confidence interval

```{r eval=FALSE}
ci_mean(student_scores$final_exam, conf_level = 0.95)
```

# Hypothesis test

```{r eval=FALSE}
t_test_helper(student_scores$final_exam, mu = 80)
```

# Regression

```{r eval=FALSE}
regression_helper(student_scores, y = "final_exam", x = "study_hours")
```

# Visualization

```{r eval=FALSE}
plot_distribution(student_scores, "final_exam")
```
